CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 26, 1956, page 15, reads: "Welcome 'Bill' - Congressman William L. Dawson of Chicago, left, seated, is welcomed by Mayor David L. Lawrence, right, seated, prior to a news conference, Tuesday. Mr. Dawson was the principal speaker at the Paul F. Jones testimonial dinner. Also present were (standing) Louis Mason, Alexander Allen, Roland Sawyer and Boyd L. Wilson, all members of the local Frontiers of America, Inc., which sponsored the dinner. - Harris Photo."David L. Lawrence was Mayor of the City of Pittsburgh 1946-1959, Governor of Pennsylvania 1959-1963, and he died in 1966.
TitMainTitle: Group seated from left: Chicago Congressman William L. Dawson, Pittsburgh Mayor David L. Lawrence; standing: members of Local Frontiers of America, Inc. Louis Mason, Alexander Allen, Roland Sawyer, and Boyd L. Wilson, gathered in Office of the Mayor, City County Building
